	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64624703">After an accident, there is a reasonable risk of a runaway fire occurring. Such fires are very difficult to put out and can take days to extinguish on their own if a proper discharge doesn't happen. There could be damage within the pack that doesn't immediately present itself. By contrast, a high-voltage power line is predictable as to how it would behave. Any fire it does create can generally be put out easily unless it's in an area that is particularly dry.</div>
	</div>

